## money-saver Design System

This project uses a custom design system derived from a **Purple Mood Board**.

### Fonts — ALWAYS use these, NEVER use Inter/Roboto/Arial/system-ui

- **Display / Numbers**: `Cormorant Garamond` (weights: 400, 500, 600; also italic)
- **Body / UI**: `DM Sans` (weights: 300, 400, 500)

**Web** (Tailwind v4): Use `font-display` and `font-sans` classes (defined in globals.css)  
**Mobile** (NativeWind): Use font family names from `tailwind.config.js` fontFamily extension

### Color Palette — Core Tokens

**Primary — Violet** (use for primary actions, nav background, default text)
- `violet-600` `#5B3FA8` — buttons, interactive elements, links
- `violet-700` `#3D2B7A` — primary text, negative amount values
- `violet-900` `#1A1235` — dark nav shell, hero backgrounds
- `violet-100` `#EAE0FB` — badges, tinted backgrounds

**Accent — Amber** (use for CTAs, income, positive amounts)
- `amber-500` `#F5A623` — CTA buttons, chart fills
- `amber-600` `#D48B0F` — income indicators, positive amounts
- `amber-400` `#FFBE4D` — highlights on dark backgrounds
- `amber-700` `#B8720A` — amber text on light backgrounds

**Support**
- `lilac-600` `#8B6BBF` — transport category, secondary charts
- `pink-500` `#D966A8` — expenses, negative amounts
- `success` `#1D9E75` — paid status, under budget
- `danger` `#D85A30` — overdue, over-budget ONLY

### Critical Color Rules

1. Income/positive amounts = `amber-600` (`#D48B0F`)
2. Expenses/negative amounts = `pink-500` (`#D966A8`)
3. Success green (`#1D9E75`) is for paid status and under-budget ONLY, NOT for income
4. Danger red only for overdue/over-budget states
5. Dark cards (`violet-900` bg) → numbers in `amber-400`, label text in `violet-300`
6. Primary actions = violet; financial CTAs (new budget, add funds) = amber

### Tailwind Usage

**Web** (Tailwind v4 — `apps/web`):
```tsx
// Use CSS variable tokens via custom classes
<div className="card">...</div>
<button className="btn-primary">...</button>
<span className="badge badge-violet">Income</span>
// Or use color utilities with the extended palette
<div className="bg-violet-900 text-violet-300">...</div>
<span className="text-amber-500">+12.4%</span>
```

**Mobile** (NativeWind v4 / Tailwind v3 — `apps/mobile`):
```tsx
// Always use className prop (never inline style for Tailwind utilities)
<View className="bg-violet-900 rounded-xl p-5">
  <Text className="font-display text-4xl text-amber-400">€ 4,820</Text>
  <Text className="font-body text-sm text-violet-300">Net balance</Text>
</View>
// NEVER: <View style={{ backgroundColor: '#1A1235' }}> for Tailwind utilities
```

### Component Patterns

**Cards**:
- Default: `card` class (web) / `bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5` (mobile)
- Dark: `card-dark` / `bg-violet-900 border border-violet-700 rounded-lg p-5`
- Lilac: `card-lilac` / `bg-lilac-50 border border-violet-200 rounded-lg p-5`
- Amber: `card-amber` / `bg-amber-50 border border-amber-300 rounded-lg p-5`

**Metric display**:
```tsx
// Always use display font for currency values
<p className="text-overline text-gray-400">Net Balance</p>
<p className="text-number text-violet-700">€ 4,820</p>
<p className="text-xs text-amber-600">↑ 8.2% this month</p> {/* Positive change */}
<p className="text-xs text-pink-500">↓ 3.4% this month</p> {/* Negative change */}
```

**Transaction amounts**:
```tsx
<Text className={amount > 0 ? 'text-amber-600 font-display' : 'text-pink-500 font-display'}>
  {amount > 0 ? '+ ' : '− '}€ {Math.abs(amount).toFixed(2)}
</Text>
```

### Editing `apps/web/src/styles.css`

This file contains **both** shadcn/ui tokens and design system tokens. When editing it:
- The `:root` / `.dark` oklch blocks are shadcn/ui — **never remove or rewrite them**
- Design system tokens (`--color-violet-*`, `--color-amber-*`, etc.) live inside the same `@theme inline` block
- `--ds-radius-*` tokens are used for design system components; `--radius-*` stay as shadcn calc() aliases
- The `body` font-family is `DM Sans` — do not revert to Poppins or Inter

### Architecture Constraints (ALWAYS respect)

1. `apps/mobile` NEVER imports `@money-saver/db` — DB has Node.js deps unavailable in RN
2. Mobile only calls APIs via `@money-saver/api-client` REST hooks
3. All DB access is server-side in `apps/web` via `createServerFn`
4. Package manager is **pnpm only** — never suggest `npm install` or `yarn`
5. Web uses Tailwind **v4**, mobile uses Tailwind **v3** (NativeWind v4 requirement)
6. Mobile forms: use `<Controller>` from react-hook-form, not `register()` (DOM-only)
7. Use `@clerk/tanstack-start` on web, `@clerk/expo` on mobile (NOT `@clerk/clerk-expo`)

